    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Wegner estimate and localisation for alloy type operators with minimal support assumptions on the single site potential
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=T%C3%A4ufer%2C+M">Matthias Täufer</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Veselic%2C+I">Ivan Veselic</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.09012v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        New unique continuation principles or uncertainty relations for linear combinations of eigenfunctions of the Laplacian on cubes from \cite{EgidiV-20} are used to prove a Wegner estimate for alloy type models along the lines of previously known proofs, e.~g.~\cite{CombesHK-07}. Due to the strong input we merely have to assume that the single site potential is lower bounded by a characteristic funct&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.09012v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.09012v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.09012v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        New unique continuation principles or uncertainty relations for linear combinations of eigenfunctions of the Laplacian on cubes from \cite{EgidiV-20} are used to prove a Wegner estimate for alloy type models along the lines of previously known proofs, e.~g.~\cite{CombesHK-07}. Due to the strong input we merely have to assume that the single site potential is lower bounded by a characteristic function of a set of positive measure. We obtain a Wegner estimate with optimal volume dependence at all energies, and localisation near the minimum of the spectrum, even for some non-stationary random potentials.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.09012v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.09012v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 16 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
