    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Analyticity and infinite breakdown of regularity in mass-subcritical Hartree scattering
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Lee%2C+G+E">Gyu Eun Lee</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08770v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We study the asymptotic behavior of solutions to the defocusing mass-subcritical Hartree NLS $iu_t + Δu = F(u) = (|x|^{-γ}*|u|^2)u$ on $\mathbb{R}^d$, $d\geq 2$, $\frac{4}{3} &lt; γ&lt; 2$. We show that the scattering problem associated to this equation is analytically well-posed in the weighted spaces $Σ= H^1\cap\mathcal{F}H^1$ and $\mathcal{F}H^1$. Furthermore, we show that the same problem fails to b&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08770v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.08770v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08770v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        We study the asymptotic behavior of solutions to the defocusing mass-subcritical Hartree NLS $iu_t + Δu = F(u) = (|x|^{-γ}*|u|^2)u$ on $\mathbb{R}^d$, $d\geq 2$, $\frac{4}{3} &lt; γ&lt; 2$. We show that the scattering problem associated to this equation is analytically well-posed in the weighted spaces $Σ= H^1\cap\mathcal{F}H^1$ and $\mathcal{F}H^1$. Furthermore, we show that the same problem fails to be analytically well-posed for data in $L^2$. This constitutes an infinite loss of regularity between the scattering problems in weighted spaces and in $L^2$. This further develops an earlier investigation initiated by the author in which a finite breakdown of regularity was proved for the $L^2$ scattering problem for the mass-subcritical NLS with power nonlinearity $F(u) = |u|^pu$.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08770v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.08770v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 15 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
    </p>
    

    
      <p class="comments is-size-7">
        

        
