    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Evolution of concentration under lattice spin-flip dynamics
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Chazottes%2C+J+-">J. -R. Chazottes</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Collet%2C+P">P. Collet</a>, 
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Redig%2C+F">F. Redig</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08264v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We consider spin-flip dynamics of configurations in $\{-1,1\}^{\mathbb{Z}^d}$, and study the time evolution of concentration inequalities. For &#34;weakly interacting&#34; dynamics we show that the Gaussian concentration bound is conserved in the course of time and it is satisfied by the unique stationary Gibbs measure. Next we show that, for a general class of translation-invariant spin-flip dynamics, it&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08264v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.08264v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08264v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        We consider spin-flip dynamics of configurations in $\{-1,1\}^{\mathbb{Z}^d}$, and study the time evolution of concentration inequalities. For &#34;weakly interacting&#34; dynamics we show that the Gaussian concentration bound is conserved in the course of time and it is satisfied by the unique stationary Gibbs measure. Next we show that, for a general class of translation-invariant spin-flip dynamics, it is impossible to evolve in finite time from a low-temperature Gibbs state towards a measure satisfying the Gaussian concentration bound. Finally, we consider the time evolution of the weaker uniform variance bound, and show that this bound is conserved under a general class of spin-flip dynamics.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08264v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.08264v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 15 March, 2021; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="comments is-size-7">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Comments:</span>
      <span class="has-text-grey-dark mathjax">24 pages, submitted</span>
    </p>
    

    

    
