    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Spectral properties and time decay of the wave functions of Pauli and Dirac operators in dimension two
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Kova%C5%99%C3%ADk%2C+H">Hynek Kovařík</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08262v2-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        In this paper we consider two-dimensional Pauli and Dirac operators with a polynomially vanishing magnetic field. The main results of the paper provide resolvent expansions of these operators in the vicinity of their thresholds with explicit expressions for all the corresponding singular terms. It is shown, in particular, that the nature of these expansions is determined by the flux of the magneti&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08262v2-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.08262v2-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08262v2-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        In this paper we consider two-dimensional Pauli and Dirac operators with a polynomially vanishing magnetic field. The main results of the paper provide resolvent expansions of these operators in the vicinity of their thresholds with explicit expressions for all the corresponding singular terms. It is shown, in particular, that the nature of these expansions is determined by the flux of the magnetic field. We also show how the magnetic field influences the time decay of the associated wave-functions quantifying thus the paramagnetic and diamagnetic effects of the spin
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08262v2-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('2103.08262v2-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 23 March, 2021; <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">v1</span> submitted 15 March, 2021;
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> March 2021.
      
