    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08224v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We consider the quantum many-body evolution of a homogeneous Fermi gas in three dimensions in the mean-field scaling regime. We study a class of initial data describing collective particle-hole pair excitations on the Fermi ball. Using a rigorous version of bosonization for non-solvable models, we prove that the many-body evolution can be approximated in Fock space norm by a quasifree bosonic evol&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.08224v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.08224v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.08224v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
        We consider the quantum many-body evolution of a homogeneous Fermi gas in three dimensions in the mean-field scaling regime. We study a class of initial data describing collective particle-hole pair excitations on the Fermi ball. Using a rigorous version of bosonization for non-solvable models, we prove that the many-body evolution can be approximated in Fock space norm by a quasifree bosonic evolution of the collective particle-hole excitations.
